s://www.888poker.es/blog/">Espa&ntilde;ol</a>                       </li>                                    <li class="menu-item">                <div class="ring r-center"></div>                         <a href="https://www.888poker.it/blog/">Italian</a>                       </li>               </ul>            </nav> </div>   </div>                            </nav>                       </details>                       <!-- end language menu -->                                           <!-- Circle Buttons -->                         <div class="headerLinks">                           <small>Dark </small>                           <input type="checkbox" hidden="hidden" id="themeswitcher">                           <label class="switch" for="themeswitcher"></label>                         </div>                       <!-- end Circle Buttons -->                      </div>                   </div>                      <!-- Long Circle Buttons -->                  <div class="col col-fixed col-long-buttons">                     <div class="button_wrapper long">                                                                     <a class="joinnow buzz-out-on-hover" href="https://www.888poker.com/openclient.htm">Play</a>                                           </div>                  </div>                 <!-- end Long Circle Buttons -->                           </div> <!-- grid -->     </div> <!-- header -->   </header>     <div class="container">     <div class="grid">       <div class="col col-12">             <div class="breadcrumb_line">                    <div class="region region--breadcrumb-line">       <div id="block-blog888new-breadcrumbs" class="block block-system block-system-breadcrumb-block">               <div class="block__content">         <nav role="navigation" aria-labelledby="system-breadcrumb">     <div id="system-breadcrumb" class="visually-hidden">You are here</div>     <ol class="breadcrumbs">        <li>         <a href="https://www.888poker.com/magazine/">Home</a>         <span class="chevron right"></span>       </li>               <li class="current">Poker Hands Ranked &ndash; What Beats What?</li>     </ol>   </nav>      </div>   </div>    </div>              </div>       </div>                <main id="main" class="col col-grow-8 col-sm" role="main">                               <div class="region region--content grid-full layout--pass--content-medium ie11-autorow" id="content">     <div data-drupal-messages-fallback="" class="hidden messages-list"></div>  <article data-history-node-id="1426" role="article" about="/magazine/how-to-play-poker/hands" class="node node--type-guide node--view-mode-full">   <header class="">                       </header>   <div class="node__content">          <div class="trinityAudioPlaceholder" style="min-height: 80px;"><div class="trinity-player-iframe-wrapper" data-player-id="33a5add41a833d9671f2aa8dbe9fc588" style="min-height: 80px; min-width: 360px;"><iframe class="trinity-iframe trinity-loader loaded" style="height: 80px;"></iframe><iframe class="trinity-iframe trinity-player trinity-player-33a5add41a833d9671f2aa8dbe9fc588" name="audioFrame_33a5add41a833d9671f2aa8dbe9fc588" src="https://trinitymedia.ai/player/trinity-player.php?pageURL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.888poker.com%2F%2Fmagazine%2Fhow-to-play-poker%2Fhands&amp;unitId=2900003515&amp;userId=7c5c1ac5-02d0-4647-b70e-26f998ab1561&amp;isLegacyBrowser=false&amp;version=20230927_957dc4656423de91eded378a40327e57027c625d&amp;useBunnyCDN=0&amp;themeId=203" title="Trinity Audio Player" allow="web-share" style="height: 80px;"></iframe></div></div> <div class="body" contentexport="mainText">             <div class="text-content field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field-item"> <h1 class="text-align-center"><span style="font-size:36px;"><strong>Poker Hands Ranked &ndash; What Beats What?</strong></span></h1>  <p>This complete list gives you the full rundown of possible hands in order &ndash; from the strongest to the weakest. Starting with the best <strong>poker hands</strong>, we&rsquo;ll explain what each looks like and which other hands they beat</p>  <ul><li><a href="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/poker-hand-ranking-770X1622_0.jpg" rel=" noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Download the Full Poker Hands Ranking</a></li> </ul><h2 id="1-royal-flush"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>1. Royal Flush</strong></span></h2>  <p><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Royal-Flush.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Royal Flush" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="46e10792-93d7-4e8d-b4ed-e192a0a91037" src="/img/Royal-Flush.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></p>  <p>Sitting at the very top of the poker hierarchy, you&rsquo;ll find the royal flush. The strongest poker hand of all is a type of straight flush where you have A-K-Q-J-10 &ndash; all in the same suit.</p>  <h4 id="what-does-royal-flush-beat"><strong>What does Royal Flush beat?</strong></h4>  <p>As the highest poker hand, a royal flush beats every other hand your opponents might hold.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="2-straight-flush"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>2. Straight Flush</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Straight-Flush.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Straight Flush" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="3076121a-8d5b-4654-b122-1242d8fb7d9a" src="/img/Straight-Flush.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></p>  <p>A straight flush is made up of five consecutive cards, all in the same suit. For example, 9-8-7-6-5 all in diamonds.</p>  <h4 id="what-does-straight-flush-beat"><strong>What does straight flush beat?</strong></h4>  <p>This beats all other poker hands, except for a higher straight flush.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="3-four-of-a-kind"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>3. Four-of-a-Kind</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Four-of-a-Kind.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Four-of-a-Kind" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="545353ec-c699-4d96-a36a-23ced0e047d2" src="/img/Four-of-a-Kind.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></p>  <p>A four of a kind in poker is simply four cards of the same value. So if you end up with 7-7-7-7-4 in your five-card hand, congratulations, you&rsquo;ve got &lsquo;quads&rsquo;!</p>  <h4 id="what-does-four-of-a-kind-beat"><strong>What does four-of-a-kind beat?</strong></h4>  <p>This is very often a winning poker hand, beating anything other than a straight/royal flush. If another player also has a four of a kind, the rank of the four cards will determine who wins. For example, J-J-J-J-4 beats A-7-7-7-7.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="4-full-house"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>4. Full House</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Full-House.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Full House" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="e28ca340-c93b-464b-a9fd-b66f640d3320" src="/img/Full-House.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></p>  <p>A full house poker hand is made up of a matching three of a kind together with a pair of a different value. For example, 10-10-10-8-8 &ndash; which is known as a &lsquo;tens full of eights&rsquo;.</p>  <h4 id="does-a-full-house-beat-a-straight"><strong>Does a full house beat a straight?</strong></h4>  <p>Yes &ndash; a full house beats a poker straight. The only hands which can beat a full house are four of a kind, straight flush or royal flush. When two people have a full house, the highest three of a kind wins. If that rank happens to be the same, the one with the highest matching pair wins the hand.&nbsp;</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="5-flush"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>5. Flush</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><strong><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Flush.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Flush" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="da2edd2d-0b7e-4344-9342-3de6c2c01f48" src="/img/Flush.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></strong></p>  <p>A flush in poker consists of five cards which are all part of the same suit, but not in a consecutive order, such as A-K-8-7-3 in hearts.</p>  <h4 id="does-a-flush-beat-a-full-house"><strong>Does a flush beat a full house?</strong></h4>  <p>No, a flush does not beat a full house &ndash; but it does beat a straight. In the case of a flush vs another flush, the hand with the highest card in the flush wins (e.g. A-10-7-4-3 of diamonds beats K-10-7-4-3 of diamonds).</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="6-straight"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>6. Straight</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><strong><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Straight_0.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Straight" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="990534fd-400b-47eb-859e-790a9ae7f7c6" src="/img/Straight_0.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></strong></p>  <p>If you have a straight, you&rsquo;ll hold five consecutive cards which are not all the same suit. For example, 8-7-6-5-4 in different suits. The highest possible straight sequence is A-K-Q-J-10.</p>  <h4 id="what-does-straight-beat"><strong>What does straight beat?</strong></h4>  <p>A poker straight always beats a 3 of a kind, two pair or a single pair. It does not beat a flush or better.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="7-three-of-a-kind"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>7. Three-of-a-Kind</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><strong><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Three-of-a-Kind_0.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Three-of-a-Kind" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="6f1b747c-c5ca-47b4-b675-07a026026b5b" src="/img/Three-of-a-Kind_0.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></strong></p>  <p>Just like its four card counterpart, a 3 of a kind consists of three cards of the same rank &ndash; for instance, your five-card hand contains 8-8-8-5-2.</p>  <h4 id="what-does-3-of-a-kind-beat"><strong>What does 3-of-a-kind beat?</strong></h4>  <p>While it might not be one of the highest poker hands, 3 of a kind still beats two pairs, one pair and high card.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="8-two-pair"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>8. Two Pair</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><strong><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/Two-Pair.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Two Pair" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="9e248853-d6c1-4910-86e5-2679b7d19466" src="/img/Two-Pair.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></strong></p>  <p>Two pair is exactly what it says on the tin &ndash; two pairs, each being a different rank. For example, 8-8-5-5-3 would be two pairs.</p>  <h4 id="what-does-two-pair-beat"><strong>What does two pair beat?</strong></h4>  <p>Two pairs are better than one, so you&rsquo;re sure to beat one pair.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="9-one-pair"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>9. One Pair</strong></span></h2>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><strong><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/One-Pair.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="One Pair" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="b5192629-5909-4370-b8d7-3782c185ab98" src="/img/One-Pair.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></strong></p>  <p>One pair is simply two cards of the same value, such as having two kings in your hand.</p>  <h4 id="what-does-one-pair-beat"><strong>What does one pair beat?</strong></h4>  <p>One pair can only beat a high card or a lower value pair. But if you bluff hard enough, it could still be a winning poker hand.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="10-high-card"><span style="font-size:24px;"><strong>10. High Card</strong></span></h2>  <p><strong><picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/High-Card_0.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="High Card" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="5c3f9e1d-ec44-426b-b9ed-1feb83338f21" src="/img/High-Card_0.jpg" width="511" height="156" loading="lazy"></source></picture></strong></p>  <p>High card is the lowest possible hand, made up of five cards which do not produce any of the above.</p>  <h4 id="what-does-high-card-beat"><strong>What does high card beat?</strong></h4>  <p>If you end up with a high card, you need to hope your opponents have this too, as even a pair beats it. When your opponents also lack so much as a pair, the highest value card wins.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h2 id="summary"><strong><span style="font-size:24px;">Summary</span></strong></h2>  <p>Poker Hand Rankings are essential when playing <a href="https://www.888poker.com/poker-games/texas-holdem/">Texas Hold'em</a>, Five Card Stud, Omaha, and your favourite poker games. Most players rarely get to form a Royal Flush, a Straight Flush, or Four of a Kind &ndash; they are scarce hands in competitions. But, sometimes, a lowly poker hand played right can help you take down monster pots. It's not always about what you're holding; it's really about how well you play the players!</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p> <picture><source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/inline-images/poker-hand-ranking-770X1622_0.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="poker hand rankings" data-entity-type="file" data-entity-uuid="397f3a4c-7aaf-42d9-96c3-a3143af1c688" height="1245" src="/img/poker-hand-ranking-770X1622_0.jpg" width="591" class="align-center" loading="lazy"></source></picture><p>&nbsp;</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p class="text-align-center"><strong>Download our <a href="https://www.888poker.com/en/poker%20hands%20ranking.pdf">poker hand rankings cheat sheet&nbsp;PDF</a> for a quick way to reference how your hand stacks up.</strong></p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p><span style='mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri'><a href="https://www.888poker.com/magazine/web-stories/poker-hands-ranked/">See your web story regarding this subject</a>.</span></p><p></p><p></p> </div>       </div>             <div class="field field--name-field-author field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__item">  <article data-history-node-id="1594" role="article" about="/magazine/author/888poker-team" class="node node--type-author node--view-mode-under-article-content">   <header class="">                       </header>   <div class="node__content">                     <div class="author_title_line filter_cat_link">           <span class="border"></span>       <span class="author_title first border-hide">  About the Author </span>        <span class="author_title second border-hide">                  See all <strong><a href="/magazine/author/888poker-team" hreflang="en">888poker Team</a></strong>   Articles                    </span>     </div>   <div class="author_details_full_block grid">       <div class="author_details_block col col-fixed col-sm">     <div class="author_name" contentexport="authorName">     <strong><a href="/magazine/author/888poker-team" hreflang="en">888poker Team</a></strong>      </div>                   <span class="field field--name-field-author-image field--type-image field--label-hidden field__item">  <a href="/magazine/author/888poker-team">  <picture>                   <source srcset="/magazine/sites/magazine.888poker.com/files/styles/author_under_article_desktop_75x75_/public/2023-05/2023-05-17_10-25-43.webp?itok=a8q9RpTv 1x" media="all and (min-width: 768px)" type="image/webp" width="75" height="75">